GitHub Commands
git init: Initializes a new Git repository in the current directory.
git clone <repo_url>: Clones an existing Git repository from a URL to your local machine.
Configuration
git config --global user.name "Your Name": Sets your username.
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com": Sets your email address.
git config --global color.ui auto: Enables color-coded output in Git.
Status and Logs
git status: Shows the working directory and staging area status.
git log: Displays a log of commits on the current branch.
git log --oneline: Shows a simplified log with each commit on one line.
Staging and Committing Changes
git add <file>: Stages a specific file.
git add .: Stages all changes in the current directory.
git commit -m "commit message": Commits staged changes with a message.
git commit -a -m "commit message": Commits all tracked changes with a message (without using git add).
Branching
git branch: Lists all branches in the repository.
git branch <branch_name>: Creates a new branch.
git checkout <branch_name>: Switches to the specified branch.
git checkout -b <branch_name>: Creates and switches to a new branch.
git branch -d <branch_name>: Deletes a branch locally.
Merging and Rebasing
git merge <branch_name>: Merges the specified branch into the current branch.
git rebase <branch_name>: Replays commits on top of another branch (used for cleaner commit history).
Undoing Changes
git reset --soft <commit_hash>: Resets the staging area to a specific commit (keeps changes).
git reset --hard <commit_hash>: Resets the working directory and staging area to a specific commit (deletes changes).
git checkout -- <file>: Discards changes in a specific file.
Pushing and Pulling
git push <remote> <branch_name>: Pushes changes from the local branch to a remote branch.
git pull <remote> <branch_name>: Pulls changes from the remote branch to the local branch.
git fetch <remote>: Fetches all changes from a remote without merging.
Remote Management
git remote add <name> <url>: Adds a new remote repository.
git remote -v: Lists all remotes and their URLs.
git remote remove <name>: Removes a remote.
Stashing
git stash: Stashes changes in a dirty working directory.
git stash apply: Re-applies the latest stash.
git stash list: Lists all stashes.
git stash drop: Deletes the latest stash.
Tags
git tag <tag_name>: Creates a tag at the current commit.
git tag: Lists all tags.
git tag -d <tag_name>: Deletes a local tag.
Viewing Differences
git diff: Shows differences between the working directory and the staging area.
git diff <branch_name>: Shows differences between the current branch and another branch.
Advanced Commands
git cherry-pick <commit_hash>: Applies a specific commit from another branch onto the current branch.
git revert <commit_hash>: Creates a new commit that undoes the changes from a specific commit.
git bisect: Helps identify a specific commit that introduced a bug by performing a binary search.
